 accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":5,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":14,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705195,"age":59,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes had at least 4 sons with John Wylley. She died after 1440, in England."},"et":{"–after 1440":"–pärast 1440","1390–1462":"1390–1462","1430–1497":"1430–1497","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1435–Male":"1435–Surnud","1440–1499":"1440–1499","–1440":"–1440","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1493":"1493","1382":"1382","say 1435":"1435","1390":"1390","1337":"1337","1435":"1435","1499":"1499","1453":"1453","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","after 1440":"pärast 1440","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1328":"1328","England":"England","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","